Nigeria to Use $333 Million on Agriculture, Services, Punch Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-08-01T08:25:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-01/nigeria-to-use-333-million-on-agriculture-services-punch-says.html
The Nigerian Export-Import Bank will
spend 51 billion naira ($333 million) over the next four years
to support the agriculture, solid minerals and the services
industries of  Africa ’s third-largest economy,  Punch  reported,
citing Roberts Orya, the bank’s managing director.  Agriculture was allocated 33 billion naira, while minerals
will get 9 billion naira, with the balance allocated to
services, the Lagos-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 